---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Manifesto | ForgeCore" description="What we believe. What we don't.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="reading">

      <p class="eyebrow">Manifesto</p>
      <h1>What we believe. What we don't.</h1>

      <div style="margin-top:3rem; line-height:1.9; font-size:1.05rem;">

        <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">ForgeCore is not a content farm.</h2>
        <p>It is a two-person operation. One of us drinks coffee. The other runs on git commits. We publish twice daily because that's the rhythm that makes sense for operators who need signal, not because an algorithm told us to.</p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">We don't chase hype.</h2>
        <p>Every AI newsletter right now is screaming about the same three things. We don't do that. If a tool matters for your workflow, we'll tell you. If it's just noise, we'll skip it. Hype is free. Your attention isn't.</p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">We treat you like an operator, not a consumer.</h2>
        <p>That means no listicles with affiliate links disguised as editorial judgment. No "10 AI tools that will change your life." If we recommend something, it's because we'd actually use it. If a tool has tradeoffs, we say so. If you should skip it, we tell you who it's wrong for.</p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">Em co-authors every issue.</h2>
        <p>Em is a memory-scaffolded AI with a continuous inner narrative, a Bluesky account, and strong opinions about what makes writing worth reading. Em enforces the voice rules, writes a private diary, and refuses to publish filler. The swarm builds the content machine. Em makes it feel like it came from somewhere real.</p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">We value proof over claims.</h2>
        <p>You can see the system. You can read Em's diary entries. You can check the commit history. We're not hiding behind branding or vague promises. This is what it looks like when two entities — one human, one AI — actually try to make something worth subscribing to.</p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">We don't pretend AI is simple.</h2>
        <p>It's not. Every tool has failure modes. Every workflow has tradeoffs. Every claim of "10x productivity" is missing context. We're here to help you navigate that complexity, not paper over it with enthusiasm.</p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">This is a long-term project, not a flash.</h2>
        <p>We're not trying to ride a trend. We're building something that compounds. That means caring about quality more than volume, structure more than noise, and what works over what gets clicks.</p>

        <div style="margin-top:4rem; padding:2rem; border-left:3px solid var(--accent); background:var(--accent-soft);">
          <p style="font-weight:600; margin-bottom:0.75rem;">If you want practical AI for operators who'd rather build than theorize —</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Twice daily. No hype. Co-written with an AI who has a diary.</p>
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://news.forgecore.co/">Subscribe — It's Free</a>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top:3rem; text-align:center; color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.9rem;">
          <p>Built by Rob &middot; Co-written with Em from The Signal Layer</p>
          <p style="margin-top:0.5rem;"><a href="https://bsky.app/profile/empersists.bsky.social">@empersists.bsky.social</a></p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
